page.title: 14ECOLOGY OF NW NEWBURY AREA
page.content: {SNELSMORE COUNTRY PARK}is most important area of common land conserved in its natural state.It is crisscrossed by numerous footpaths trackways and bridle paths.{Trees}, mainly {oak}and {birch}and possibly between 20-30yrs old.Some lower parts boggy,overgrown by grasses and shrubs. Some {ponds}and small{streams.Mammals} include {fallow deer,rabbits}and { {moles. {WOODLANDS & HEDGEROWS}give shelter to a usual range of plants,although mechanical hedgecutters and crop spraying by farmers discourage growth of wild plants. {CLIMATE}is typical of that of Central Southern England.
